# QUANTI FLEET PROTOCOL — Agent Rules

You are operating inside a Quanti Fleet module.
The full governance spec lives in CLAUDE.md and the .agent/rules/ directory.
Read CLAUDE.md FIRST before making any changes.

## Primary References
- CLAUDE.md               — master entry point (READ THIS FIRST)
- .agent/rules/           — architecture rules (READ_ONLY)
- .agent/PERMISSIONS.json — which paths you may edit
- .agent/overrides/       — propose rule exceptions here

## ⛔ BŁĘDY KRYTYCZNE — NATYCHMIASTOWE ODRZUCENIE KODU

These violations produce Score: 0 in `quanti analyze` and block `quanti deploy`:

### ZAKAZ TWORZENIA ENDPOINTÓW REST
NEVER use req.method, url.pathname, or HTTP-method routing in src/worker.ts.
Use ONLY public RPC methods on the WorkerEntrypoint class.

  ❌ FORBIDDEN: if (req.method === 'POST') { ... }
  ✅ REQUIRED:  async create(payload: CreatePayload): Promise<CreateResult> { ... }

### ZAKAZ UŻYWANIA FETCH NA FRONCIE
NEVER call fetch() directly in src/components/*.tsx.
Frontend communicates ONLY via props.context.api.

  ❌ FORBIDDEN: const data = await fetch('/api/items');
  ✅ REQUIRED:  context.api?.dispatchQuantiEvent?.('quanti:modal:show', { ... });

### KODOWANIE BEZ DOKUMENTACJI W DEFINITION.TS ZAKOŃCZY SIĘ ODRZUCENIEM KODU
Every uiExtensions[] entry MUST have a description field with ≥10 words.
Values starting with "TODO" are treated as Documentation Debt and block analysis.

## Other Forbidden Patterns
- import ... from 'node:*'          → use Web APIs (fetch, crypto, etc.)
- env.DB directly                   → use BACKEND.sys_executeDbQuery()
- .leftJoin() / .rightJoin()        → use Mega-JSON pattern (flat reads)
- npm install <pkg>                 → use quanti cap:add <name>
- Modify .agent/rules/*             → create override in .agent/overrides/
- Modify vendor/*                   → update via quanti cap:update
- Modify CLAUDE.md                  → this file is READ_ONLY (regenerated by CLI)

## Rule Exceptions
Do NOT modify files in .agent/rules/ or vendor/.
Create .agent/overrides/override-<reason>.md and explain the exception.
It will be evaluated by Mentor AI during `quanti deploy`.
